      "text": "Fuel pump removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Fire is strictly prohibited. ​",
        "Removal should be performed with the engine stopped and the battery (-) terminal disconnected. ​"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Fuel pressure Removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000474",
          "label": "Fuel pressure Removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Passenger side front seat removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000792",
          "label": "Passenger side front seat removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Maintenance Lid removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "488_3.0_jpn_11034665_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the maintenance lid (A) and disconnect the coupler (B). Breather Tube (C), Disconnect the quick-connect fuel tube (D).",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000483",
          "label": "Disconnect the quick-connect fuel tube (D).",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Lock nut removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "488_3.0_jpn_11034666_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the locknut (A) of the fuel pump with the special tool."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Fuel pump removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "488_3.0_jpn_11034667_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the fuel pump (A) from the fuel tank."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Be careful not to bend the float arm of the sender unit."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Fire is strictly prohibited. ​",
        "Removal should be performed with the engine stopped and the battery (-) terminal disconnected. ​"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Fuel pump installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "488_3.0_jpn_11034668_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Insert the fuel pump into the fuel tank with the new fuel pump packing (B) inserted into the fuel pump (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When inserting the fuel pump packings into the fuel pump, be careful not to damage the packings.",
        "Be careful not to bend the float arm of the sender unit."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "When inserting the fuel pump packings into the fuel pump, be careful not to damage the packings."
        },
        {
          "text": "When inserting the fuel pump packings into the fuel pump, be careful not to damage the packings."
        },
        {
          "text": "Be careful not to bend the float arm of the sender unit."
        },
        {
          "text": "Be careful not to bend the float arm of the sender unit."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "488_3.0_jpn_11034669_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Install the fuel pump packings (A) on the fuel tank side. Align the alignment mark (B) on the fuel pump with the alignment mark (C) on the fuel tank, and push the fuel pump vertically until the fuel pump is tight against the packing."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Make sure that the fuel pump packings are not misaligned or engaged. If it is misaligned or engaged, it may lead to fuel leakage."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Lock nut Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "488_3.0_jpn_11034670_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install new fuel pump locknut (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Lock nut Tightening"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "488_3.0_jpn_11034671_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Tighten the fuel tank locknut (A) with the dedicated tool."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "After tightening the fuel tank lock nut, the alignment marks (B) on the fuel pump and fuel tank should align."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Maintenance Lid Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "488_3.0_jpn_11034672_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Breather Tube (A), Connect the quick-connect fuel tube (B). Connect the coupler (C). When the 12V battery negative (-) terminal is connected and the ignition is turned to the ON mode (never turn the starter), the fuel pump operates for about 2 seconds to increase the fuel pressure in the fuel line system. Repeat this operation 2-3 times and check for fuel leaks in each part of the fuel piping system. Install the maintenance lid (D).",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000483",
          "label": "Connect the quick-connect fuel tube (B).",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Passenger side front seat installation",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000792",
          "label": "Passenger side front seat installation",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
